{'body': 'My current group is too small to worry about thanking them in any =20\r\nmajor way.  Of we all thank each other.  We have 4 regular volunteers =20=\r\n\r\nand currently having a different member each month volunteering to do =20=\r\n\r\na presentation.  Only occasionally having an outside speaker. =20\r\nSometimes via iChat.\r\n\r\nWhen I was with HAUS in Honolulu, we thanked the volunteers by buying =20=\r\n\r\nthem pizza each month at the board meetings.  In Boston, we had an =20\r\nannual meeting of "activists".  400 strong.  Then we had an annual =20\r\npicnic for volunteers as well.\r\n\r\nI think it never hurts to thank people every chance you can get.\r\n\r\nLynn\r\n\r\n\r\n"Sometimes I wonder whether the world is being run by smart people who =20=\r\n\r\nare putting us on or by imbeciles who really mean it." --Mark Twain\r\n\r\nLynn Wegley\r\nlynnw3@csmining.org\r\nhttp://www.ugnn.com\r\n\r\nOn Apr 30, 2010, at 12:38 AM, Nicholas Pyers wrote:\r\n\r\n> Here in Australia, May 10th to 16th, 2010 is National Volunteer Week =20=\r\n\r\n> (NVW) =96 the largest celebration of volunteers and volunteerism in =20=\r\n\r\n> Australia, and it provides an opportunity to highlight the role of =20\r\n> volunteers in our communities and to say thank you to the more than =20=\r\n\r\n> 5 million Australians who volunteer.\r\n>\r\n> Earlier this week I asked Australian Apple User Groups if they were =20=\r\n\r\n> doing anything to thank their volunteers, and in light of Chris =20\r\n> Hart\'s query about ways of getting people onto Boards & Committees =20\r\n> and my response about thanking outgoing Committee members, I thought =20=\r\n\r\n> now would also be an appropriate time to share the article with =20\r\n> everyone here.\r\n>\r\n> The article provides some ideas on WHO to thank; HOW to thank them; =20=\r\n\r\n> and WHEN it may be appropriate to thank them.\r\n>\r\n> You can read the article over at;\r\n> http://www.appleusers.org/ugr/have-you-thanked-your-volunteers/\r\n>\r\n> If your group has done something different or interesting to thank a =20=\r\n\r\n> member of your group, perhaps you\'ll share the idea with the list :)\r\n>\r\n> --\r\n> Nicholas Pyers (nicholas@appleusers.org)\r\n> Founder & Publisher, AppleUsers.org\r\n>\r\n> http://www.appleusers.org/\r\n>\r\n>\r\n>\r\n>\r\n>\r\n> _______________________________________________\r\n> Do not post admin requests to the list. They will be ignored.\r\n> Augd mailing list      (Augd@lists.apple.com)\r\n> Help/Unsubscribe/Update your Subscription:\r\n> http://lists.apple.com/mailman/options/augd/lynnw3%40aol.com\r\n>\r\n> This email sent to lynnw3@aol.com\r\n\r\n _______________________________________________\r\nDo not post admin requests to the list. They will be ignored.\r\nAugd mailing list      (Augd@lists.apple.com)\r\nHelp/Unsubscribe/Update your Subscription:\r\nhttp://lists.apple.com/mailman/options/augd/mlsubscriber.tech%40csmining.org\r\n\r\nThis email sent to mlsubscriber.tech@csmining.org\r\n\r\n', 'subject': 'Re: AUGD: Have You Thanked Your Volunteers?'}